revision.text:
[[ZDoom]] introduced automatic compatibility with known troublesome maps in [[version history#2.3.0|version 2.3.0]]. The following maps are currently identified:

* ''6pack2.wad'' MAP02: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Alien Vendetta''
: MAP07: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
: MAP15: [[compatibility options#compat_trace|Self ref. sectors don't block shots]]
* ''Archie'' MAP01: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Astrostein'' MAP01 to MAP10: [[compatibility options#compat_spritesort|Invert sprite sorting]]
* ''Astrostein 2'' MAP01 to MAP09: [[compatibility options#compat_spritesort|Invert sprite sorting]]
* ''Astrostein 3'' MAP10, MAP13 to MAP15, MAP17 and MAP20: [[compatibility options#compat_spritesort|Invert sprite sorting]]
* ''[[Cheogsh]]'' MAP01: Adjust the z-height of the {{Class|BlueSkull|blue skull key}} so it is spawned properly on top of the [[3D floor]]
* ''[[Cheogsh 2]]'' MAP04: Adjust the z-height of the actors in the {{Class|megasphere}}'s cage so they are spawned properly on top of the [[3D floor]]
* ''Claustrophobia 1024'' MAP01: [[compatibility options#compat_badangles|Cannot travel straight NSEW]]
* ''Community Chest'' MAP29: [[compatibility options#compat_wallrun|Enable wall running]]
* ''Community Chest 3'' MAP03: [[Sector_CopyScroller]] effect added to emulate side effects of a [[Boom]] bug
* ''[[Daedalus: Alien Defense]]'' MAP04 and MAP24: activation method for non-pushable, push-activated lines changed
* ''Dark Side of the Mind'': [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''[[Doom]]'' E3M4: [[Monster]]-activated, single-use [[Door_Raise]] changed to [[Door_Open]] so that half the level is not randomly blocked off
* ''[[Doom II]]'' MAP27: A one-way teleporter is no longer an unreachable secret 
* ''Doom: Rampage Edition'' MAP01: Teleport tags are ignored to emulate an old ZDoom bug
* ''Doomsday of UAC'': [[compatibility options#compat_anybossdeath|Allow any bossdeath for level special]]
* ''Eternal Doom'' MAP25: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Eternal Doom I-II-III'':
: MAP25: [[compatibility options#compat_stairs|Use buggier stair building]] and [[compatibility options#compat_maskedmidtex|Ignore Y offsets on masked midtextures]]
: MAP28: [[compatibility options#compat_trace|Self ref. sectors don't block shots]] and [[compatibility options#compat_useblocking|All special lines can block <use>]]
* ''The Evil Unleashed'' E3M4: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
* ''The Final Gathering'' MAP05: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''The Garrison'': force node rebuilding
* ''[[Hacx]]'' MAP03 and MAP17: [[compatibility options#compat_useblocking|All special lines can block <use>]]
* ''[[Happy Time Circus]]'': Teleport tags are ignored to emulate an old ZDoom bug
* ''Hell Revealed'':
: MAP19: [[compatibility options#compat_limitpain|Limit Pain Elementals' Lost Souls]]
: MAP26: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and raised ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Hell to Pay'' MAP14 and MAP22: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''[[Hexen]]: Deathkings of the Dark Citadel'' MAP54: activation method for non-crossable, cross-activated lines changed
* ''Icarus: Alien Vanguard'' MAP24: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Imp's are Ghost Gods'' MAP01: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Khorus'' MAP08: kludge for a voodoo doll on conveyor belt
* ''[[Massmouth 2]]'': Player speed reset bug and slope overflow bug reestablished
* ''Mayhem 2013'' MAP05: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Memento Mori'' MAP29: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
* ''Memento Mori 2''
: MAP03 and MAP25: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
: MAP12: [[compatibility options#compat_badangles|Cannot travel straight NSEW]]
* ''Noob Project Part 5'' MAP02: Teleport tags are ignored to emulate an old ZDoom bug
* ''Nuke Mine''
: E1M2: flawed teleporters disabled
: E1M4: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
* ''Phobos'' MAP03: [[compatibility options#compat_floormove|Use Doom's floor motion behavior]]
* ''Plutonia 2'' MAP32: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Project X'' MAP14: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Real World'' MAP11: [[compatibility options#compat_trace|Self ref. sectors don't block shots]]
* ''Requiem'':
: MAP04: [[compatibility options#compat_useblocking|All special lines can block <use>]]
: MAP23: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Reverie'' MAP18: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Rock and Roll Rebel Radio Against Satan City'' MAP01: Teleport tags are ignored to emulate an old ZDoom bug
* ''seej.wad'' MAP01: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Squadron 417'' MAP21: [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished
* ''Strain'':
: MAP02: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
: MAP07: Flag 1 cleared from linedef 1021
: MAP13: [[compatibility options#compat_spritesort|Invert sprite sorting]]
: MAP31: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
* ''Slaughter Until Death'' E2M6: [[compatibility options#compat_shorttex|Find shortest textures like Doom]]
* ''[[Super Sonic Doom]]'' MAP31: Properly unfreezes the player after finishing the first bonus stage.
* ''Suspended in Dusk'' MAP01: [[compatibility options#compat_sectorsounds|Sector sounds use center as source]]
* ''TNT: Evilution'' MAP31: Fixes the yellow key not appearing in single-player mode.
* ''[[Town Infection]]'' MAP17: Teleport tags are ignored to emulate an old ZDoom bug
* ''UAC Ultra'' MAP07: [[Sector_CopyScroller]] effect added to emulate side effects of a [[Boom]] bug
* ''[[Ultimate Simplicity]]'' MAP07: Lines 397 and 411 are set to cause monsters in sector 17 to be alerted after said sector becomes accessible so they successfully teleport in for battle
* ''[[Void]]'': Slope overflow bug reestablished, and some pillars slightly squashed
* ''The Waterfront'': [[compatibility options#compat_corpsegibs|Crushed monsters can be resurrected]] and ghost monster bug reestablished

Note that compatibility options that aren't linked but are described as "bug reestablished" are not, and will not be, available as normal compatibility options. They rely on the engine behaving in a fundamentally broken fashion and should not be used anymore.

Maps that are not linked above were not made specifically for ZDoom.

